I agree that the "white-out" style is awful, although in a grayscale manga, it isn't quite as out of place as a solid black fill, but I feel that a partial censor like this is still worse. At least with the whiteout/blackout censorship, it's consistent; with this, it's not only absurd and obtrusive, it's half-assed to boot. That said, those are my thoughts on the matter, and since either style tends to ruin doujinshi for me, it's kind of a moot point, for my purposes... "You can kill my boner with fire, or you can kill my boner with censorship. My boner's just as dead either way." ‹--- ...I'm pretty sure that's how the saying goes.
